false,"model_progress":[0.032982,0.067223,0.083336,0.095284,0.09873,0.10029,0.10221,0.10041,0.095768,0.086684,0.075826,0.061256],"unified_progress":[0.035086,0.067046,0.083361,0.092743,0.099527,0.10165,0.10239,0.10215,0.097482,0.092667,0.074498,0.051405]},{"section":9,"text":"Lower motor neurons control the muscles directly, so if they're damaged, you get fasciculations, which are those little muscle twitches.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036559,0.065301,0.081217,0.092752,0.098331,0.10036,0.10345,0.1012,0.096631,0.086918,0.075648,0.06163],"unified_progress":[0.034054,0.06487,0.083852,0.095104,0.10188,0.10484,0.10334,0.10117,0.098775,0.089456,0.072029,0.050628]},{"section":10,"text":"The patient's speech impairment suggests that there might be involvement of the bulbar muscles, which control speech and swallowing.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037216,0.061991,0.076485,0.085884,0.094509,0.098516,0.10181,0.10152,0.099106,0.092689,0.081849,0.068423],"unified_progress":[0.037,0.064404,0.080437,0.091224,0.097753,0.10317,0.10152,0.10034,0.097254,0.091952,0.076252,0.058695]},{"section":11,"text":"That's often seen in diseases affecting the lower motor neurons, like amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS).","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03078,0.059722,0.075551,0.087797,0.095149,0.099582,0.10709,0.10784,0.10187,0.092601,0.078222,0.063787],"unified_progress":[0.030178,0.058822,0.081179,0.094192,0.099971,0.11142,0.10708,0.10398,0.097894,0.090965,0.07224,0.052075]},{"section":12,"text":"ALS is a condition where both upper and lower motor neurons degenerate, leading to muscle weakness, fasciculations, and eventually, respiratory failure because the muscles involved in breathing stop working.","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040647,0.057395,0.070281,0.080064,0.091035,0.096843,0.10437,0.10631,0.10294,0.093377,0.084408,0.072334],"unified_progress":[0.043432,0.066869,0.080502,0.090186,0.096543,0.10338,0.10144,0.10024,0.095966,0.088599,0.07459,0.058245]},{"section":13,"text":"The autopsy findings of ventral root atrophy also point towards a lower motor neuron issue.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03057,0.054564,0.072469,0.083259,0.092334,0.096725,0.10082,0.1006,0.09905,0.095991,0.089709,0.083904],"unified_progress":[0.033511,0.060681,0.077689,0.088172,0.094764,0.098455,0.097892,0.097647,0.09779,0.092364,0.084322,0.076714]},{"section":14,"text":"Ventral roots are where the lower motor neurons exit the spinal cord, so atrophy there would mean those neurons are degenerating.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032159,0.056521,0.074664,0.08847,0.097711,0.10186,0.10656,0.10412,0.10047,0.090508,0.079795,0.067154],"unified_progress":[0.032821,0.064335,0.08454,0.097752,0.10421,0.10632,0.10333,0.098908,0.098371,0.085367,0.070158,0.053894]},{"section":15,"text":"In ALS, both upper and lower motor neurons are affected, but the lower ones are often more prominently involved early on.","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031769,0.051048,0.068703,0.081475,0.093928,0.10039,0.10661,0.10788,0.10622,0.097555,0.08556,0.068864],"unified_progress":[0.034046,0.061013,0.079831,0.091948,0.099612,0.10897,0.10402,0.10142,0.09787,0.091262,0.074242,0.055769]},{"section":16,"text":"Putting it all together: weakness, fasciculations, speech issues, and ventral root atrophy.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0347,0.06754,0.07051,0.070093,0.077335,0.08065,0.084618,0.089663,0.091133,0.095193,0.11162,0.12694],"unified_progress":[0.068192,0.097578,0.085717,0.08209,0.081487,0.083466,0.082229,0.086469,0.082852,0.081214,0.082996,0.085711]},{"section":17,"text":"That sounds a lot like ALS.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034636,0.11468,0.12236,0.13327,0.10043,0.087118,0.080421,0.